5
00:00:33,430 --> 00:00:33,997
Baby boy.

6
00:00:38,102 --> 00:00:38,742
P'Mum.

7
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:41,820
It's okay.

8
00:00:44,652 --> 00:00:45,877
I really miss you.

9
00:00:47,667 --> 00:00:48,871
I do miss you, too.

10
00:00:49,784 --> 00:00:50,886
I miss you so much.

11
00:00:58,699 --> 00:01:00,040
Where have you been?

12
00:01:01,719 --> 00:01:03,192
Will you come to see me again?

13
00:01:09,273 --> 00:01:10,026
I will.

14
00:01:10,336 --> 00:01:11,265
I must come.

15
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,037
I will come here to help you.

16
00:01:13,364 --> 00:01:14,361
I give you my word.

17
00:01:21,009 --> 00:01:22,524
I know that you will always
keep your promise.

18
00:02:35,755 --> 00:02:37,117
Speak now.

19
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,156
Why did you call me so late?

20
00:02:39,643 --> 00:02:41,144
It is not "happen anywhere".

21
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,826
Huh? Wait!

22
00:02:43,989 --> 00:02:44,695
What are you talking about?

23
00:02:46,054 --> 00:02:47,871
About the thing that I crossed
to another dimension to meet Dew.

24
00:02:48,747 --> 00:02:50,077
I have tried it here.

25
00:02:51,093 --> 00:02:52,365
But I was not going anywhere.

26
00:02:53,866 --> 00:02:56,478
Mum, I think you should get some sleep.

27
00:02:56,616 --> 00:02:57,867
So you will recover from your injury soon.

28
00:02:59,434 --> 00:03:00,497
I can't do that.

29
00:03:01,152 --> 00:03:02,792
Dew doesn't have much time now.

30
00:03:03,630 --> 00:03:04,671
If I don't go there...

31
00:03:04,825 --> 00:03:05,510
Dew might...

32
00:03:28,476 --> 00:03:29,465
Cancel everything.

33
00:03:33,684 --> 00:03:35,406
Is your nephew okay?

34
00:03:36,731 --> 00:03:37,795
How is Dew?

35
00:03:37,895 --> 00:03:39,205
He is safe.

36
00:03:41,488 --> 00:03:42,376
Thank you so much.

37
00:03:42,832 --> 00:03:43,673
It's okay now.

38
00:03:43,832 --> 00:03:45,202
I will take it from there.

39
00:03:47,098 --> 00:03:47,720
Yes, sir.

40
00:04:59,264 --> 00:05:03,359
=609 Bedtime Story=

41
00:05:03,646 --> 00:05:07,943
(Episode 9)
(On the first day we say goodbye)

42
00:05:07,943 --> 00:05:08,609
What?

43
00:05:08,818 --> 00:05:09,958
Why are you so surprised?

44
00:05:10,344 --> 00:05:12,643
I just asked you to take me home.

45
00:05:14,063 --> 00:05:15,654
I understand you, P'Mum.

46
00:05:15,872 --> 00:05:17,426
But your doctor hasn't said

47
00:05:17,543 --> 00:05:18,969
you could go home yet.

48
00:05:19,055 --> 00:05:20,460
That means you asked me

49
00:05:20,460 --> 00:05:22,660
to help you escape from the hospital.

50
00:05:22,871 --> 00:05:23,719
But I am worried.

51
00:05:26,794 --> 00:05:28,175
I don't know how it is going.

52
00:05:32,005 --> 00:05:33,180
But you told me that

53
00:05:33,606 --> 00:05:35,184
on the first day when you met him,

54
00:05:35,184 --> 00:05:36,785
he was already shot.

55
00:05:38,255 --> 00:05:39,791
He might not get shot yet.

56
00:05:40,388 --> 00:05:41,446
If I could come back to help him
just in time...

57
00:05:42,976 --> 00:05:44,244
I do want to help you.

58
00:05:44,725 --> 00:05:46,034
But you are not healed yet.

59
00:05:46,444 --> 00:05:47,822
Mint is very serious about this.

60
00:05:48,653 --> 00:05:50,167
You know your sister so well.

61
00:05:53,863 --> 00:05:54,806
Whatever it takes,

62
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:57,017
I really want to meet Dew.

63
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:58,355
Dew?

64
00:05:59,444 --> 00:06:00,299
Is his name Dew?

65
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:02,753
Yes.

66
00:06:05,505 --> 00:06:06,187
Why?

67
00:06:07,484 --> 00:06:08,164
Nothing.

68
00:06:08,445 --> 00:06:10,004
I just feel a little strange.

69
00:06:10,412 --> 00:06:11,890
Your boy from the other universe

70
00:06:11,890 --> 00:06:13,823
and Mint's boyfriend have the same name.

71
00:06:17,239 --> 00:06:18,422
Is her boyfriend's name Dew too?

72
00:06:18,708 --> 00:06:19,305
Yes.

73
00:06:22,669 --> 00:06:23,801
What does he look like?

74
00:06:24,216 --> 00:06:25,111
Do you have his photo?

75
00:06:25,575 --> 00:06:27,518
I have already sent you his photo.

76
00:06:27,596 --> 00:06:28,524
Don't you remember?

77
00:06:29,057 --> 00:06:30,370
Do you have dementia?

78
00:06:30,456 --> 00:06:31,023
Huh?

79
00:06:32,143 --> 00:06:33,070
Hey, Mum.

80
00:06:33,271 --> 00:06:34,753
Here's the photo of your
future brother-in-law,

81
00:06:34,753 --> 00:06:36,467
so you'll know what he looks like.

82
00:06:46,819 --> 00:06:48,001
Yes, P'Vee.

83
00:06:50,079 --> 00:06:50,975
Okay.

84
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,527
Yes, all right.

85
00:06:53,030 --> 00:06:53,766
Yes.

86
00:06:57,789 --> 00:06:59,488
I have to go and help P'Vee.

87
00:06:59,773 --> 00:07:00,965
Can you stay alone here?

88
00:07:02,671 --> 00:07:04,135
Yes, I can.

89
00:07:04,234 --> 00:07:04,919
Are you sure?

90
00:07:06,562 --> 00:07:07,191
Yes.

91
00:07:08,476 --> 00:07:09,222
I will leave now.

92
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:33,322
(Games: Mum, Mint took a man here.
I took a picture of him for you.)

93
00:07:39,995 --> 00:07:40,673
Wait.

94
00:07:42,065 --> 00:07:43,106
What?

95
00:07:43,106 --> 00:07:43,912
Are you serious about this guy?

96
00:07:44,967 --> 00:07:45,662
Who?

97
00:07:46,144 --> 00:07:46,766
Well...

98
00:07:46,957 --> 00:07:48,278
I mean the brand's owner.

99
00:07:49,081 --> 00:07:51,331
You look so happy with him.

100
00:07:51,395 --> 00:07:53,085
It's nothing serious.

101
00:07:53,085 --> 00:07:55,046
I always take good care of my clients.

102
00:08:02,016 --> 00:08:02,784
Is your girlfriend calling?

103
00:08:04,719 --> 00:08:05,798
Dew, you can pick up,

104
00:08:05,798 --> 00:08:06,726
if you want to.

105
00:08:06,726 --> 00:08:07,532
I can wait.

106
00:08:08,101 --> 00:08:08,942
If I take this call,

107
00:08:09,728 --> 00:08:10,783
will you feel sad?

108
00:08:11,362 --> 00:08:12,177
I will.

109
00:08:13,144 --> 00:08:14,843
I don't want to lie to her.

110
00:08:26,046 --> 00:08:26,903
What's up?

111
00:08:27,164 --> 00:08:27,770
P'Games,

112
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:29,581
just promise me

113
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:32,753
that you won't tell anyone
that I will go to meet Dew.

114
00:08:34,412 --> 00:08:35,211
Why's that?

115
00:08:36,337 --> 00:08:37,630
You must promise me that.

116
00:08:39,013 --> 00:08:39,882
All right.

117
00:08:39,882 --> 00:08:41,318
I give you my word.

118
00:08:42,698 --> 00:08:43,937
If you slip your tongue,

119
00:08:44,624 --> 00:08:45,678
I will beat you.

120
00:08:46,338 --> 00:08:47,357
Okay, I will not...

121
00:08:48,503 --> 00:08:49,396
What the heck?

122
00:08:49,714 --> 00:08:51,011
He just hung up on me like that.

123
00:09:02,522 --> 00:09:04,206
Sorry that you have to wait so long.

124
00:09:04,491 --> 00:09:05,217
P'Vee.

125
00:09:07,092 --> 00:09:08,537
Are you really sure

126
00:09:08,592 --> 00:09:09,756
that you want to do this?

127
00:09:12,157 --> 00:09:12,719
Yes.

128
00:09:19,228 --> 00:09:19,900
Let's go.

129
00:09:42,859 --> 00:09:44,352
Games and I are not in a relationship.

130
00:09:45,758 --> 00:09:46,408
Well, I already knew

131
00:09:47,117 --> 00:09:48,729
that you just wanted to get back to me.

132
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:56,354
Just like you and I
are not in a relationship too.

133
00:09:57,404 --> 00:09:58,519
Come on, Vee.

134
00:09:59,351 --> 00:09:59,986
Look,

135
00:10:00,827 --> 00:10:02,430
we were together for 5 years.

136
00:10:02,956 --> 00:10:05,185
We built this company,
and we shared a dream.

137
00:10:06,472 --> 00:10:07,914
Do they really mean nothing to you?

138
00:10:11,147 --> 00:10:12,418
That sounds familiar.

139
00:10:15,357 --> 00:10:16,784
I said the same words to you,

140
00:10:20,802 --> 00:10:22,644
when you asked me to let you go
so that you could get married.

141
00:10:23,962 --> 00:10:25,068
What did you say that day?

142
00:10:29,048 --> 00:10:29,842
I have to do that.

143
00:10:32,661 --> 00:10:33,668
Have to, right?

144
00:10:34,129 --> 00:10:36,105
Now I know I was wrong.

145
00:10:39,707 --> 00:10:40,538
Vee.

146
00:10:47,754 --> 00:10:49,338
You should quit doing this.

147
00:10:52,561 --> 00:10:55,655
From the way people look at us,
we've already had a bad reputation.

148
00:10:58,358 --> 00:11:01,668
We don't need a complicated relationship
to make things worse.

149
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:04,965
I love you.

150
00:11:06,959 --> 00:11:07,996
I do love you.

151
00:11:10,132 --> 00:11:10,840
Vee.

152
00:11:20,423 --> 00:11:22,590
You should go back and take
the responsibility of your choice.

153
00:11:25,892 --> 00:11:27,536
I will never forget

154
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:30,773
how much I loved you.

155
00:11:34,142 --> 00:11:35,312
But that was all in the past.

156
00:11:39,835 --> 00:11:41,197
You have to let me go.

157
00:11:41,197 --> 00:11:41,873
No.

158
00:11:43,003 --> 00:11:43,702
Never.

159
00:11:48,293 --> 00:11:50,464
What you're doing is such a burden to me.

160
00:11:55,603 --> 00:11:57,181
I need my life back.

161
00:12:30,912 --> 00:12:31,443
Here.

162
00:12:32,826 --> 00:12:33,494
Your ice-cream.

163
00:12:35,357 --> 00:12:36,473
After the battle,

164
00:12:36,473 --> 00:12:37,482
you need to obtain some more energy.

165
00:12:37,981 --> 00:12:38,637
Thanks.

166
00:12:39,651 --> 00:12:40,629
Do you like it?

167
00:12:46,047 --> 00:12:47,251
I do like ice cream.

168
00:12:50,282 --> 00:12:52,340
But thank you for telling me
to confront the truth

169
00:12:52,625 --> 00:12:53,580
in this case.

170
00:12:59,443 --> 00:13:00,065
All right.

171
00:13:02,157 --> 00:13:03,965
What you just did is so cool.

172
00:13:04,002 --> 00:13:04,633
Do you know that?

173
00:13:05,877 --> 00:13:06,651
I do know that.

174
00:13:07,402 --> 00:13:08,386
Wow!

175
00:13:09,175 --> 00:13:11,414
You need to act a little bit humble.

176
00:13:13,042 --> 00:13:14,947
I don't need to because I am a cool guy.

177
00:13:34,392 --> 00:13:35,269
Is my face dirty?

178
00:13:35,913 --> 00:13:36,621
Yes.

179
00:13:37,549 --> 00:13:38,260
Is it clean now?

180
00:13:39,853 --> 00:13:40,660
A little bit right.

181
00:13:40,897 --> 00:13:42,183
- Right?
- There. Right there.

182
00:13:42,354 --> 00:13:43,003
There.

183
00:13:43,202 --> 00:13:43,993
Right here?

184
00:13:44,112 --> 00:13:44,959
Yes.

185
00:13:45,064 --> 00:13:45,800
It's on my right side

186
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:47,173
or your right side?

187
00:13:47,987 --> 00:13:48,854
My right side.

188
00:13:48,854 --> 00:13:49,618
Right.

189
00:13:49,618 --> 00:13:50,667
My right side?

190
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:43,802
Can I go home tomorrow?

191
00:14:47,990 --> 00:14:48,910
Easy, easy.

192
00:14:50,352 --> 00:14:51,391
Are you okay?

193
00:14:51,391 --> 00:14:52,156
Yes, I am.

194
00:14:52,156 --> 00:14:53,468
- All right.
- It hurts.

195
00:14:53,586 --> 00:14:54,553
You will go home soon.

196
00:14:55,946 --> 00:14:58,031
If I did not miss the flight that day,

197
00:14:58,031 --> 00:14:59,250
you wouldn't have to...

198
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:00,054
Look...

199
00:15:00,889 --> 00:15:01,923
Don't think like that.

200
00:15:02,642 --> 00:15:03,952
It's not what you think.

201
00:15:05,355 --> 00:15:07,355
You knew who did that to me.

202
00:15:16,699 --> 00:15:17,630
I feel

203
00:15:18,284 --> 00:15:20,665
I am such a lousy brother.

204
00:15:22,482 --> 00:15:23,941
Don't think about yourself that way.

205
00:15:24,420 --> 00:15:25,013
Huh?

206
00:15:28,138 --> 00:15:29,657
If you ask me...

207
00:15:30,891 --> 00:15:33,122
I have never seen anyone
love Mint as much as you do.

208
00:15:38,552 --> 00:15:40,035
What should I do?

209
00:15:42,105 --> 00:15:43,798
I am worried about that boy so badly.

210
00:15:45,042 --> 00:15:46,188
If I could go back to that world,

211
00:15:46,895 --> 00:15:49,472
I might help him catch the murderer
that killed him.

212
00:15:51,754 --> 00:15:54,183
But I don't want to betray Mint.

213
00:15:54,326 --> 00:15:54,939
Mum.

214
00:15:55,595 --> 00:15:58,633
You always live your life
with your instinct.

215
00:16:00,074 --> 00:16:01,231
And this time,

216
00:16:01,649 --> 00:16:03,097
what does your instinct tell you?

217
00:16:24,548 --> 00:16:26,073
Why did you bring so many things here?

218
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:28,119
They are your clothes.

219
00:16:28,568 --> 00:16:30,063
I took them from your condo.

220
00:16:30,063 --> 00:16:30,937
It should be enough for you.

221
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:34,395
Mint.

222
00:16:35,729 --> 00:16:37,298
I will go back to my room.

223
00:16:38,817 --> 00:16:39,880
I am an adult now,

224
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:41,550
and I can take care of myself.

225
00:16:43,052 --> 00:16:44,419
How can you do that?

226
00:16:44,896 --> 00:16:46,204
Look at yourself now.

227
00:16:47,067 --> 00:16:48,299
You'd better stay with me.

228
00:16:50,398 --> 00:16:51,143
Why?

229
00:16:51,392 --> 00:16:52,948
You don't want to sleep on my sofa?

230
00:16:54,682 --> 00:16:56,080
My condo has two bedrooms.

231
00:16:59,431 --> 00:17:00,752
Why are you so headstrong?

232
00:17:02,404 --> 00:17:04,671
Then you should not be so stubborn.

233
00:17:07,030 --> 00:17:08,270
Once you fully recover,

234
00:17:08,428 --> 00:17:09,781
I will let you go home.

235
00:17:10,483 --> 00:17:11,936
Just not now.

236
00:17:14,083 --> 00:17:16,136
Hey, let me tell you something.

237
00:17:17,251 --> 00:17:18,834
If you do recover completely,

238
00:17:19,176 --> 00:17:21,043
I'll even let you ride your motorcycle.

239
00:17:26,144 --> 00:17:27,488
But you need to wear this.

240
00:17:28,825 --> 00:17:29,851
If your motorcycle collapses,

241
00:17:30,074 --> 00:17:31,847
it will keep you safe and sound.

242
00:17:35,814 --> 00:17:36,887
Here.

243
00:17:37,384 --> 00:17:38,076
Is it nice?

244
00:17:49,224 --> 00:17:50,030
P'Mum,

245
00:17:51,108 --> 00:17:51,985
what's wrong?

246
00:17:52,594 --> 00:17:53,270
P'Mum!

247
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:57,072
Nothing.

248
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,112
Hi. I thought we'd miss you.

249
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:13,052
Our staff said that
they will visit you at Mint's condo.

250
00:18:15,338 --> 00:18:17,144
Hey, Mint.
You and I have the same mind.

251
00:18:18,068 --> 00:18:19,462
What makes you think that?

252
00:18:21,665 --> 00:18:23,024
This helmet.

253
00:18:23,196 --> 00:18:25,153
The old one has been damaged.

254
00:18:25,438 --> 00:18:26,689
So, I bought a new one for you.

255
00:18:26,868 --> 00:18:27,876
Do you like it?

256
00:18:31,094 --> 00:18:32,204
Yes, that's right.

257
00:18:32,204 --> 00:18:32,907
It matches that coat.

258
00:18:32,907 --> 00:18:33,594
They look nice.

259
00:18:41,447 --> 00:18:42,391
No!

260
00:19:25,331 --> 00:19:29,201
(Mum's World)
(21 November 2022)

261
00:19:36,462 --> 00:19:38,302
Are the medicines too strong for you?

262
00:19:39,571 --> 00:19:40,880
You look so dull all day.

263
00:19:46,277 --> 00:19:47,022
I think so.

264
00:19:47,798 --> 00:19:48,956
It may be too strong for me.

265
00:19:50,426 --> 00:19:52,189
Or...

266
00:19:52,658 --> 00:19:53,588
Are you thinking about someone?

267
00:20:01,003 --> 00:20:01,980
Just eat.

268
00:20:03,441 --> 00:20:04,018
Come on.

269
00:20:12,469 --> 00:20:14,270
Don't die before me.

270
00:20:16,659 --> 00:20:17,731
What did you say?

271
00:20:18,822 --> 00:20:20,207
I am not dying.

272
00:20:20,207 --> 00:20:20,862
Come on.

273
00:20:22,273 --> 00:20:23,781
If you are gone,

274
00:20:26,002 --> 00:20:27,041
I can't stand living alone.

275
00:20:32,216 --> 00:20:33,362
What makes you think of that?

276
00:20:35,870 --> 00:20:36,431
Well,

277
00:20:37,220 --> 00:20:38,661
when our parents passed away,

278
00:20:40,338 --> 00:20:42,709
if you did not move from Khon Kaen
to stay with me,

279
00:20:44,385 --> 00:20:45,357
I probably could not make it.

280
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:48,547
Who told you that?

281
00:20:49,860 --> 00:20:50,959
I moved here,

282
00:20:51,635 --> 00:20:54,805
Because I wanted to live in Bangkok.
I did not want to live in Khon Kaen.

283
00:20:55,478 --> 00:20:57,438
Life is better here.

284
00:20:59,529 --> 00:21:00,597
Really?

285
00:21:10,461 --> 00:21:11,832
You have to stay with me.

286
